{"questionId":"2716490","questionHtml":"<p>Events <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> are such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>|</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substitutes into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> to form</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitutes into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>|</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math> to form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to combine their two probability equations to form an equation in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The above two <em><strong>A</strong></em> marks are awarded independently.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>correct equation in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>(or equivalent)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>75</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>5</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2716490","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ2.3","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Events A and B are such that P(A)=0.4, P(A|B)=0.25 and P(A∪B)=0.55. Find P(B).","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"3","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}